  "generated_text": "To determine how many years it takes for Carlos to start earning money, we need to compare the **Cost** to the **Revenue** for each year.\n\n**1. Define the variables and costs:**\n*   **Planting Cost:** $\\$90$ (One-time cost).\n*   **Annual Watering/Feeding Cost:** $\\$3$ per year.\n*   **Lemon Yield:** 7 lemons per year.\n*   **Sale Price per Lemon:** $\\$1.50$.\n\n**2. Calculate the annual profit:**\nFirst, let's calculate how much money Carlos makes from selling lemons in one year.\n$$ \\text{Revenue} = 7 \\text{ lemons} \\times \\$1.50/\\text{lemon} = \\$10.50 $$\n\nNext, add the annual operating cost to find the net profit for the year.\n$$ \\text{Net Profit} = \\text{Revenue} - \\text{Operating Cost} $$\n$$ \\text{Net Profit} = \\$10.50 - \\$3 = \\$7.50 $$\n\nSo, for every year after planting, Carlos earns a profit of $\\$7.50$.\n\n**3. Calculate the break-even year:**\nThe question asks when he \"starts earning money.\" This implies we need to find the point where the total revenue exceeds the total cost (Planting + Operating).\n\n*   **Year 0 (Planting):**\n    *   Cost: $\\$90$\n    *   Revenue: $\\$0$\n    *   Net: $\\$0 - \\$90 = -\\$90$ (Loss)\n\n*   **Year 1:**\n    *   Cost: $\\$90$ (planting) + $\\$3$",
